# Fluff Date: 2026-02-12 20:24:28
overview:<p>The Raijin II emerged in 3066 as the Word of Blake's comprehensive answer to the original Raijin's identified combat deficiencies. Following heavy losses among Raijin pilots during Operation Odysseus, Blakist engineers conducted extensive analysis of combat recordings and pilot interviews, identifying thin armor, ammunition dependence, and insufficient long-range firepower as critical weaknesses. Under the direction of Precentor Martial Cameron St. Jamais, the RJN-200 program delivered both field refit packages for existing units and new-production models incorporating advanced Blakist technology.</p><p>The upgrade program bore similarities to the Draconis Combine's Project Phoenix approach, providing simplified installation requirements to minimize downtime. Krupp Armament Works on Terra and Martinson Armaments served as primary production sites, with the most elite Blakist militia divisions receiving variants equipped with Capellan-developed stealth armor whose acquisition method remained a matter of speculation.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Raijin II retains the Vlar 300 XL engine and Rawlings 60 jump jets of its predecessor, maintaining the same impressive mobility profile. The most significant structural change is the adoption of a Krupp 200-ES endo steel chassis, which saves weight for additional armor and equipment. Eleven tons of Krupp Standard Plate armor with CASE protection dramatically improves survivability over the original Raijin's ferro-fibrous plating, giving the design a visually distinct and more robust appearance.</p><p>The primary armament centers on a Blankenburg 200 ER PPC paired with three Diverse Optics Sunbeam ER medium lasers, replacing the original's pulse lasers with extended-range models for greater engagement flexibility. A Holly Streak SRM-4 provides efficient close-range missile support while reducing ammunition dependency compared to the original's dual launcher configuration. Triple Strength Myomers allow the 'Mech to reach speeds of up to 119 kilometers per hour when running hot, adding a significant tactical dimension.</p><p>The incorporation of an improved C3 computer enables the Raijin II to function as part of networked combat formations, sharing targeting data with allied units. This combination of enhanced armor, improved weapons, electronic warfare capability, and conditional speed boost made the Raijin II a considerably more dangerous opponent than its predecessor.</p>

deployment:<p>Combining the best features of the 200-A and 200-B, this sniper variant pairs the ER PPC and Triple Strength Myomers of the baseline model with the light engine, stealth armor, and ECM suite of the reconnaissance variant. Armed with an ER PPC and two ER medium lasers alongside an improved C3 computer, the 200-C represents one of the most capable sniper platforms when operating within a C3-networked formation. As with the 200-B, the stealth armor and C3 system cannot operate simultaneously, requiring tactical judgment about when to employ each capability. The variant saw allocation alongside the 200-B to the Word of Blake's most elite formations.</p>

history:<p>The Raijin II program began as both a field refit initiative and a new production line in early June 3066, with upgrade packages shipping to Word of Blake Militia units across the Blake Protectorate. Production halted at Krupp Armament Works on Terra to incorporate the new specifications, while Martinson Armaments established auxiliary production lines on both Terra and Caph for the stealth armor-equipped variants. The First and Sixth Militia divisions received the bulk of the advanced 200-B and 200-C variants, while standard 200-A refits were distributed more widely.</p><p>During the Jihad, the Raijin II served as a mainstay of Blakist medium 'Mech formations, with its improved C3 integration making it particularly effective in coordinated Level II operations. The design saw extensive combat throughout the Blake Protectorate's defense and various Blakist offensive operations, with Com Guard and Blakist Raijins frequently clashing against one another during the bitter internecine fighting that characterized the conflict.</p><p>The fall of the Word of Blake brought production to a complete halt. With Krupp's facilities on Terra coming under Republic of the Sphere control and Martinson's Caph facility similarly changing hands, no faction retained both the manufacturing capability and doctrinal interest to continue Raijin II production. The remaining units gradually attrited through combat losses and parts shortages, becoming increasingly rare on the battlefields of the Dark Age and ilClan eras.</p>

